Almirall SA, Galp Energia SGPS: Iberian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-02-16T19:35:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/almirall-sa-galp-energia-sgps-iberian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spain and Portugal trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  climbed 2.1 percent to 11,047.80.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index  advanced 1 percent to 8,117.49.  Spanish stocks:  Almirall SA (ALM SM): The Spanish drugmaker said its
Sativex drug won approval for public financing in Spain. It is
the first cannabis-derived treatment to be approved in the
country, the company said in a regulatory filing. The shares
dropped 0.1 percent to 8.80 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  Galp Energia SGPS SA (GALP PL): Eni SpA Chief Financial
Officer Alessandro Bernini told analysts the company is in no
rush to sell its stake in Galp, Portugal’s biggest oil company.
Galp rose 0.2 percent to 15.54 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
